# REST API Automation Framework  
### Postman Â· Newman Â· GitHub Actions

A production-style **REST API automation framework** built using **Postman** and **Newman**, with **CI/CD execution via GitHub Actions**.  
This project demonstrates real-world API testing practices including CRUD validation, negative testing, schema/contract validation, performance checks, and secure secrets management.

---

## ğŸš€ Key Highlights

- End-to-end REST API automation using Postman
- Structured test suites: Sanity, Positive, Negative, Contract & Performance
- Full CRUD coverage (GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE)
- Schema / contract validation to detect breaking changes
- Authentication & authorization testing (Bearer token)
- Response time (performance) assertions
- CLI execution using Newman
- CI/CD integration via GitHub Actions
- HTML execution reports as CI artifacts
- Secure handling of secrets (no credentials committed)

---

## ğŸ§° Tech Stack

| Tool | Purpose |
|----|----|
| **Postman** | API request creation & test scripting |
| **Newman** | CLI runner for Postman collections |
| **GitHub Actions** | CI/CD execution |
| **Node.js** | Runtime environment |
| **HTML Reporter** | Test execution reports |

